    "body": "## Problem\r\n`test/functional/lua/fs_spec.lua` uses the return value of `vim.fs.root()` to compare the paths. But it can't resolve symlinks. So when the path involves symlinks, the same path may be represented in different forms. The symlink loop test also created the loop base on the symlink path, making the test fail.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nIn `test/testutil.lua`, `eq_paths()` is introduced as a helper function to compare two paths. This function uses `vim.uv.fs_realpath()` to normalize the relevant paths(which may contain symlinks) before comparison.\r\n\r\nResolve: #38247",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-12T09:46:19Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
